<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,927,1493]" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">
This species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[517,599,927,953]" name="Taiwan" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
by Moulton as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1908" box="[770,887,927,952]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Phyllothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citricornis">
<emphasis box="[770,887,927,952]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">citricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="ThripsWiki" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1032,1192,927,953]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Gynaikothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1192,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Gynaikothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but was subsequently transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uzel" authorityYear="1895" box="[427,530,963,989]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[427,530,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, it thus became a homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hood" authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1908" box="[1009,1196,963,989]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Phyllothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citricornis">
<emphasis box="[1009,1126,963,988]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">citricornis</emphasis>
Hood
</taxonomicName>
from North America that had previously been described in 
<emphasis box="[573,719,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Phlyllothrips</emphasis>
, a genus now recognized as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uzel" authorityYear="1895" box="[1196,1299,999,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1196,1299,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As a result, a new name is proposed here for the species described by Moulton from 
<collectingCountry box="[965,1051,1035,1061]" name="Taiwan" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="367" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,927,1493]" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis box="[199,422,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[586,677,1071,1097]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="18" pageNumber="367" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
. Brown; antennal segment I and most of II brown, same colour as head, III–VI and basal half of VII yellow, distal half of VII and all of VIII greyish brown; all three pairs of legs brown with yellow tarsi; fore wings hyaline; major body setae hyaline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,927,1493]" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">
Head about twice as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[580,663,1179,1205]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[171,1423,192,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[151,1436,181,1468]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Liothrips threobrevis nom.nov.: (78) head; (79) pronotum; (80) mesopresternum; (81) pelta; (82) tergite II; (83) shape of antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416403/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
), po setae on middle of dorsum, about 0.8 times length of eyes; maxillary stylets present only in posterior fourth of head, about 1/3 of head apart; antennal segment III 2.2 times, IV 1.8 times as long as II (
<figureCitation box="[371,454,1251,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[171,1423,192,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[151,1436,181,1468]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Liothrips threobrevis nom.nov.: (78) head; (79) pronotum; (80) mesopresternum; (81) pelta; (82) tergite II; (83) shape of antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416403/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
). Pronotal am setae (1 or 2 pairs) much shorter than aa setae (
<figureCitation box="[1146,1231,1251,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[171,1423,192,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[151,1436,181,1468]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Liothrips threobrevis nom.nov.: (78) head; (79) pronotum; (80) mesopresternum; (81) pelta; (82) tergite II; (83) shape of antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416403/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
); mesopresternum boat-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[301,383,1287,1313]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[171,1423,192,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[151,1436,181,1468]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Liothrips threobrevis nom.nov.: (78) head; (79) pronotum; (80) mesopresternum; (81) pelta; (82) tergite II; (83) shape of antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416403/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
), connected in middle; metanotum covered with dense longitudinal striae. Pelta triangular with sharp lateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[383,466,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[171,1423,192,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[151,1436,181,1468]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Liothrips threobrevis nom.nov.: (78) head; (79) pronotum; (80) mesopresternum; (81) pelta; (82) tergite II; (83) shape of antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416403/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
); tergite II laterally with 4 accessary setae (
<figureCitation box="[953,1037,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[171,1423,192,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[151,1436,181,1468]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Liothrips threobrevis nom.nov.: (78) head; (79) pronotum; (80) mesopresternum; (81) pelta; (82) tergite II; (83) shape of antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416403/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
); tube shorter than head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,927,1493]" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">
