<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="367" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,927,1493]" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1431,1457]" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hood)" baseAuthorityName="Hood" box="[643,884,1431,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Phyllothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citricornis">
<emphasis box="[643,793,1431,1456]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">L. citricornis</emphasis>
(Hood)
</taxonomicName>
mainly by having shorter maxillary stylets and shorter pronotal aa and am setae. The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2020" box="[644,769,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="threobrevis">
<emphasis box="[644,769,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="367">threobrevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates these characteristics.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
